description:
In mid-2013, it was announced that Jeff Lemire and Mike McKone would become the new creative team of Justice League of America following the conclusion of Forever Evil and would retitle the book as Justice League of Canada for an arc which would lead into something bigger down the line. After the initial announcement, plans were changed and instead of retiling Justice League of America, DC decided to cancel the title and launch Justice League United as its own stand-alone title, still starring the originally planned Canadian based Justice League team.

The roster consists of Martian Manhunter, Stargirl, Animal Man, Green Arrow, Adam Strange, Supergirl, Hawkman and the newly created Equinox. Lemire created Equinox to be a character that represents the Cree natives of Canada. While researching Cree culture, Lemire took many trips to the Cree community known as Moose Factory where he would study, teach children art classes, and get input from Cree community of what they'd like to see in a character that represented their culture.

Collected Editions

  • Vol. 1: Justice League Canada (#0-5)
  • Vol. 2: The Infinitus Saga (#6-10)
name: Justice League United

description:
Four issue mini-series.

Born in the early 1800s, Liesel Van Helsing is the daughter of the famed vampire slayer Abraham Van Helsing. Liesel, as both a genius inventor and a skilled hunter, became known as the scourge of the Underworld when she created steam-powered devices to dispatch her prey. Back then, Liesel was unbeatable… but what about now? After spending more than a century trapped in a hellish dimension called the Shadowlands, Liesel has returned to Earth and is beginning her life anew. Dedicated to not only taking out vampires, Helsing occasionally fights all kinds of evil alongside her friend Sela Mathers and the other Realm Knights sworn to protect Earth. However, a powerful evil from the past has been waiting in the shadows for his chance at a reckoning… and that chance has arrived. This is the story of Liesel Van Helsing… vampire hunter.

Collected in Grimm Fairy Tales presents Helsing: The Darkness and the Light.
name: Grimm Fairy Tales presents Helsing
